snippet.textDisplay:
I've had diagnosed when i was 7 yrs old.
I never succeed in school, since day one in elementary school i dropped from the train.
After 27 years of ADHD it's been a ride, after i got the medication for it, things been different.
Now i'm a rising esports player, i make some beats and lyrics for my first mixtape what i've been making like a year now.
I learned how to use Unreal Engine 4, Blender and World Machine, but school is always hard for me.
Feels so shit that normal things doesn't make me euphoric, it's like all others get happy from small things or get a feeling of success if they pass a test or something.
I know that sometimes i have said to people that why i'm not succeeding that it's my ADHD but i think the real reason was that i just thought it was it.
No.
It was me thinking that ADHD will reduce my talent in things. But i just do only those things what i think are fascinating, math i don't like so i don't do it if i don't have to, but making beats, lyrics, maps in unreal engine, playing with my team, it's completely different.


I want to be better and maybe i will.


PS. Good song.
